Package DDS

Interface Summary
Cache A Cache gathers a set of DLRL objects that are managed, published and/or subscribed consistently.
CacheAccess This class encapsulates the access to a set of objects.
CacheBase The CacheBase defines the common interface for all cache-like classes.
CacheListener The CacheListener is a callback interface that can be implemented by the application if it wants to be notified of incoming changes to the Cache when it is set in the updates_enabled mode.
Collection A Collection is the interface that must be implemented by all collection types (Lists, Maps and Sets).
Contract The current implementation does not yet support the notion of a Contract, so no operations in this interface are supported.
FilterCriterion A FilterCriterion is the interface that must be implemented by typed Filter criterion classes.
ObjectListener The ObjectListener interface is an abstract interface that represents a generic callback mechanism that is invoked when an ObjectHome manipulates the lifecycle of a related object.
QueryCriterion The current implementation does not yet support the notion of a QueryCriterion, so no operations in this class are supported.
Selection A Selection provides the means to designate a subset of DLRL object instances of a specific type.
SelectionCriterion A SelectionCriterion is the interface that must be implemented by all criterion types (Filters and Queries).
SelectionListener The current implementation does not yet support the notion of a SelectionListener, so no operations in this class are supported.
 

Class Summary
CacheFactory This class represents a singleton factory that allows the creation and deletion of DLRL Cache objects.
CacheKind The CacheKind class represents an enumeration of the possible types (sub classes) of a CacheBase.
CacheUsage The CacheUsage class represents an enumeration of the possible usages of a CacheBase.
CriterionKind The CriterionKind class represents an enumeration of the possible types (sub classes) of a Criterion.
DCPSState The DCPSState class represents an enumeration of the possible states in which the publication and subscribtion infrastructure used by the DLRL can be.
DLRLOid This class represents the DLRL Object Identifier, which is the unique identifier for a DLRL Object.
IntMap The IntMap is an abstract class that represents a Map that can store elements identified by an Integer key type.
List The List class is not supported.
MembershipState The MembershipState class represents an enumeration of the possible states of a member of a Selection.
ObjectHome For each application defined class there is an ObjectHome instance, which exists to globally represent the related set of instances and to perform actions on it.
ObjectRoot The ObjectRoot is the abstract root for any DLRL class.
ObjectScope The ObjectScope class represents an enumeration of the possible scopes in which to view a DLRL object.
ObjectState The ObjectState class represents an enumeration of the possible life cycle states of a DLRL object.
ReferenceScope The ReferenceScope class represents an enumeration of the possible scopes in which to view a relation.
Set The Set is an abstract class that represents a Set that can store any number of elements in an un-ordered way.
StrMap The StrMap is an abstract class that represents a Map that can store elements identified by a String key type.
 

Exception Summary
AlreadyDeleted Thrown to indicate that the object on which an operation was accessed has already been deleted.
AlreadyExisting Thrown to indicate that the object being created already exists.
BadHomeDefinition Thrown to indicate that an invalid home definition was found or that there was a mismatch between two ObjectHomes.
BadParameter Thrown to indicate that an invalid parameter was passed to an operation.
DCPSError Thrown to indicate that an error occured in the DCPS layer.
InvalidObjects Thrown to indicate that the one or more objects within a cache access has invalid relations.
NoSuchElement Thrown to indicate that the element requested does not exist within the collection.
NotFound Thrown to indicate that the related object being navigated to cannot be resolved by the DLRL.
PreconditionNotMet Thrown to indicate that a specific precondition for the invoked operation has not yet been met.
SQLError Thrown to indicate that there was an invalid SQL expression used.
